node.text: Team work, dedication, patriotism, and a family spirit are at the core of our company. I will never turn my back on them and neither will they. It’s this bond, which allows us to persevere through this storm 🇺🇸

node.title: My business was built on American values.

node.text: Short clip of my daughter Clover’s recent homeschool project interviewing former President Donald Trump. I want Clover to listen to all sides of the Political spectrum then choose for herself. Big thanks to President Trump for taking the time to do this. Could not have been more respectful and kind to my kid. Next up First Lady Michelle Obama, a strong female role model for my daughter for sure.

node.text: When I went to Africa this past year it opened my eyes to the plight of people in this amazing Continent. I toured Gifted Hands Educational Centre, a school for children in the most ravaged and poorest part of Kenya. The school was feared to close, the teachers had not been paid in 7 months ( amazingly showing up to work still) and the kids having hardly any food to eat. After pulling the director aside I asked how much does it cost for the full yearly budget to run the school including food and pay for the teachers. After him huddling with his staff he told me $50000. That’s $50000 to take care of almost 300 kids every Day for the year ! Got this horrible guilt feeling in my stomach as I have spent money on some of the stupidest material things when people have no money, food or education. I promised the school I would take care of them for the rest of my life, and Clover, my daughter, would continue after me. This trip put so much in perspective for me. I just didn’t visit, I followed up on my promises to these forgotten kids. I just got this amazing video from them and wanted to share. Let’s all try to give a little extra today in any way we can ❤️

node.text: Came out to Vegas for 24 hour whirlwind trip to surprise one of my dearest and trusted friends @nicksantonastasso for his birthday. We were all able to keep it a secret, which made it even more special. If you don’t follow @nicksantonastasso - you should as he’s one of the most inspiring humans that I’ve ever met ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Weitsman on May 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
I typically keep these types of things private, but I want to share this story on here. This relationship was created from a random DM that caught my eye on social media last week. Someone alerted me to the plight of this young teenage girl, Payton, who has been diagnosed with a severe and rare form of childhood bone cancer known as Ewing’s Sarcoma. She has been in the hospital receiving chemotherapy for the past year and needed a way to get home to surprise her family for the weekend. I could not go personally, so I sent my pilots to make her weekend a little bit better :) There’s a lot of people out there that are blessed with more than one person could need, including myself, and it is our responsibility to help others in anyway, and every way we can. 

To whom much is given, much will be required.

node.text: Most people know I don’t follow politics much and I never comment when other people share their political opinions. But I do want my daughter Clover to know what’s going on in the world, and to pay attention to decisions that are made and the people who make them. As part of her home schooling she’s interviewing various leaders of both parties to find out what’s really going on in the world and she’s starting at the highest level of government. I’m grateful that former President Donald Trump agreed to meet with Clover today and answer pressing questions that are on the minds of many people in her age group. This is not about politics but about understanding all viewpoints. I can’t begin to tell you how proud I am of my daughter for her questions and composure talking with a world leader.

node.text: Happiness for me is all about meeting good people in this world.  Relationships and moments trump material things each and every time. @swaelee
